<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="113" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,827]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,766,791]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Etymology.</emphasis>
This new species is a patronym named in honor of David Faulkner of 
<collectingRegion box="[1137,1253,766,791]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">California</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1265,1325,767,791]" name="United States of America" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">USA</collectingCountry>
. Faulkner has been a mentor to the first author over the years and was the first to introduce him to forensic entomology.
</paragraph>
